        You remember.
        I know you do.
}
I miss that place.
Or maybe just how it felt. {
    ?: I do too.
    ?: Is that all that's left for you?
        Please don't.
        Don't make me answer that.
        -> gameover
}
# Launching into house recollection, branches based on established info from earlier...
[match:window_reason_given]
    =true
        I loved how the morning light would come in.
        It brought our whole world to life.
        Especially you, 
        You would never close the blinds.
        Then each morning you'd spring up with the sun.
        That certainly made me a more lively person too...
        I could sleep for days,
        without you to wake me up.
        Or to keep me going...
        ...
    =false
        It was... nice.
        Quiet, quaint.
        Always felt like somewhere you could stay
        ...
        You always seemed so comfortable there.
        ...
[/match]
We fell into a routine pretty quickly,
didn't we? {
    ?: Like clockwork
}
# The cafe was NOT near this house, but she will fasely put these two memories together.
Yeah, haha.
It all blurred together after a while,
but I remember the order of it.
Wake up,
You would take your time getting ready-
as always-
then out the door...
[match:cafe_mentioned]
    =true
        towards the café.
        Didn't even have to think about it.
