[/match]
It all felt... easy.
Like we had already figured it out.
Didn't have to think about anything.
That was the nice part.
Although...
Didn't start that way, haha.
Remember the first few nights?
Nothing was really unpacked yet,
just enough to pretend that we were settled.
Those boxes sat by the door for days!
[match:house_confronted]
    =true
        Not a thing was unpacked until you knew exactly where you wanted it. {
            ?: You're mixing it up again...
                Please...
                Maybe I am.
                ...
                Things don't stay where I leave them anymore.
                ...
                Maybe that is why I keep holding them here.
                The places, the order of it.
                If I let go,
                everything runs together again.
                Please,
                stay a little longer.
                Help me keep it in one piece.
                -> sculpt_alt_end
            ?: (Say nothing)
        }
    =false
        Not a thing was unpacked until you knew exactly where you wanted it.
[/match]
Heh,
Maybe that's what I actually miss.
The feeling of things falling into place,
not the routines or memories themselves...
But the fact that I built them with you.
Hey, you know...
-> ending_lie

# Confrontation, leads to true ending.
[block:confront]
    Why would you ask me that? <face:anger_sfrown> {
        ?: Humor me.
            [match:name_shared]
                =true
                    Is this some sort of joke? <face:anger_grimace>
