[block:ending_truth]
    ...
    I don't remember your name.
    But I remember... you.
    I remember how you made me feel.
    It's just-
    ...
    I'm sorry.
    ...
    I have been playing these moments back for so long.
    Over and over.
    None of it stays where it belongs anymore.
    Places keep folding into each other.
    Mornings into nights.
    Houses into cafés.
    You into a memory.
    ...
    I-
    I just wanted something new,
    Something I have not already recycled.
    ...
    Everything feels so worn down.
    I am sorry this is all that's left of me.
    ENDING 2: FRAGMENTS <signal:ending> {
        ?: Play again?
            -> intro
    }
[/block]

# Capture for fallthroughs into gameover, hopefully we never see this
# But I want to handle it gracefully just in case...
What is...
# --- Default game-over that we can jump to from essentially anywhere.
@gameover
# make sure you reset game state on gameover so the try again is truly fresh.
SESSION TERMINATED <signal:gameover> <face:error> {
    ?: Try again
        -> intro
}